					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1436137&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182915" alt="fieldstone" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1436137)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;" >fieldstone</a></span> <span class="odate time_1503805632 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Aug 2017 03:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3579357">
									

<p>The highly contagious weird property with the ectoplasm felt like misdirection that made the computer's disarming personality a more effective twist. I liked the interview log, where the little guy just wants to impress his friend and doesn't know he's doing anything wrong.</p>
<p>The UIU file was cool, I always like to see how different GOIs react to objects. I think it would help the readability of the article if this and the interview were behind labeled blocks &#8212; I'm not sure if that's possible with all the formatting on the UIU report, and it's a minor thing anyway, but seeing the addenda laid out up front would have helped it all come across more immediately for me.</p>
<p>All in all I love it though. It would be fun to do a tale where things go terribly wrong with their network and they have to ask The Ghost for help getting it under control (or a simulation where they make it think that's happening) &#8212; I bet it would just love to help out its buddies however it could, and try <em>really</em> hard to stay focused and not mess with any of the shiny, fun-looking things it saw along the way&#8230;</p>

							</div>

								
					
