														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3579518">
									

<p>I feel like this is a retread of various other anomalous computer viruses/software on the site, without enough content to differentiate itself. It could be interesting with more personality, but not enough time is spent on that.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the <strong>consequences</strong> of introducing SCP-633 to the concept of 'newer' computers in a way it could fully understand may cause unforeseen <strong>consequences</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Imma leave this here.</p>
<p>Not a fan of the Foundation using words like &quot;supernatural&quot; (that's more or less redundant with 'anomaly') or &quot;ectoplasm&quot;, and I find it hard to believe that records of UIU-held anomalies can be obtained via a federal information act like that.</p>

							</div>

								
					
